{"key":"post-12082190","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12082190</id>\n<content>No.&amp;nbsp; Misting pins directly does not cause them to abort.&amp;nbsp; You're &lt;i&gt;supposed to mist&lt;/i&gt; the pins and mushrooms as they grow.&amp;nbsp; The horrible advice to avoid misting came from ten or more years ago when people were writing 'teks' to name after themselves and one of them was for a totally sealed up terrarium.&amp;nbsp; It even had a 'drip shield' to prevent water from dripping on the mushrooms.&amp;nbsp; Performance was horrible and molds usually won the day back then.&amp;nbsp; Today, we know far more about growing mushrooms thanks to those of us who constantly experiment with new things.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Having standing water after misting for over half an hour indicates insufficient fresh air, which when coupled with wet fruits tends to abort pins.&amp;nbsp; Dunking overnight does not cause aborts.&amp;nbsp; Those are the facts.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12082196</next>\n<prev>12082174</prev>\n<first>12076480</first>\n<last>15055197</last>\n<when>1266941734</when>\n<utime>02/23/10 06:15 PM</utime>\n</post>"}